SOURCE
https://www.newscientist.com/article/2151268-an-ai-has-learned-how-to-pick-a-single-voice-out-of-a-crowd/
AGENT
Niels Meinke
GOAL
To solve the noisy coctail problem.It means identify a specific voice among a crowd.
DATA
The algorithm trained using 100 English speakers.
METHOD
They used deep clustering to identify matchles voiceprint of 100 English speakers.
RESULTS
The system is now able to differentiate two people speaking into same microphone with 90 percent accuracy. If the number of speaker is increasing, the percent is still up to 80.
COMMENTS
It is pretty amazing to see this kind of success rate, if you consider even humans can have a hard times about classifying voices and faces.